data.name: Jarvis
data.description: üì¶ Jarvis, a forward-thinking tech startup, empowers users to achieve their project goals within set timeframes by addressing common hurdles like motivation, overthinking, and time management. data.description: ‚öôÔ∏è This project involves designing a web application for the school board of an international literary festival to facilitate the planning of author interventions in various settings. The application records data of speakers, their works, and languages spoken, allowing management of requests from participating establishments. Features include submission of wishes by establishments, intervention planning considering logistical constraints, and generating statistics for monitoring festival editions. Development entails using PostgreSQL for the database and an appropriate programming language, with a focus on SQL scripts to ensure system functionality.

data.name: TourismDatabase
data.description: üöÄ This project aims to redesign the website of a region to enhance the presentation of available tourist offerings. A database will be created to reference attractions, accommodations, and restaurants, each with specific characteristics such as contact information, hours of operation, photos, and user ratings. Attractions encompass various types of activities with detailed descriptions, accommodations are categorized into several types with comprehensive pricing information, while restaurants are characterized by cuisine type and price category.
